Hello Team,

I had resolved the issue by uninstalling podman 4.3.1 and installing 4.1.0 version and now it is working as expected.

Now i tried with simple DB connect bean in Java and build an image.. 

C:\Users\ssamsudeen2>podman run -p 8080:8080 -d dbconnect:1.0
cfbc0c8fbe263d3ff35786c4b55968eb9b90f68ca75f8d6555e3adf580c2d586

Log:
C:\Users\ssamsudeen2>podman logs cfbc0c8fbe263d3ff35786c4b55968eb9b90f68ca75f8d6555e3adf580c2d586
Feb 06, 2023 5:32:29 PM com.gxo.podman.db.connect.ConnectDB main
INFO: Getting connection...
Feb 06, 2023 5:32:35 PM com.gxo.podman.db.connect.ConnectDB main
INFO: Unable to process java.sql.SQLRecoverableException: IO Error: The Network Adapter could not establish the connection

Docker file:
FROM docker.io/openjdk:17-jdk-alpine
VOLUME /tmp
EXPOSE 8080
ADD DBConnectivity.jar DBConnectivity.jar
ENTRYPOINT ["sh", "-c", "java -jar DBConnectivity.jar"]

I am calling DB through VPN and not sure if we need to add any other steps to make this DB successful from podman desktop to external DB connection.

Code:
public class ConnectDB {

	private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(ConnectDB.class.getName());  
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Connection conn = null;
		try {
            Class.forName("oracle.jdbc.driver.OracleDriver");
        } catch (ClassNotFoundException e) {
            logger.info("Where is your Oracle JDBC Driver?" + e.getMessage());
            e.printStackTrace();
            return;
        }

		try {
			logger.info("Getting connection...");
			String url = "jdbc:oracle:thin:@*******:****:****";
			Properties props = new Properties();
			props.put("user", "*******");
			props.put("password", "********");
			props.put("SetBigStringTryClob", "true");
			conn = DriverManager.getConnection(url, props);
			conn.setAutoCommit(true);
			logger.info("Got connection!" + conn);
		} catch (Exception e) {
			logger.info("Unable to process "  + e);
		}
	}
}
